column5: Wow! Sometimes the truly big ones are not that nice to look at, but that is a beautiful fish.
Great catch folks, and its nice to see a big fish been held the right way, instead of the Bass guys with the arms out vertical hold, with the jaw bent
Holy smokes what a huge looking smallie !!!!
Good for his guiding promo for sure!
Amazing fish. Good job for letting her go. Great pics
The smallie with the looks of a hog! Great fish and colours!
More of a rugby ball.
Here the video of it! http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l1yU0WKkpEw&feature=player_embedded
Paul is great guy to be fishing with. Knows his stuff. My avatar pic is my 1st Lake Trout caught with him. That's one heck of a smallie! (Kind of an oxymoron)
gigantic
Wow !!!! some big fish coming out of the river lately, congrats!!!
What a monster, bet that fight was amazing.  Congrats to her!!!
Wow! Great Fish!
Great video clip. Now you know what cloud 9 feels like eh

I saw this thing in person and I am glad I had the opportunity !!  Honestly, the pics and even the video do not do it justice !... this thing was a beeeeeeast !!  I knew something was up when I got the frantic phonecall...."hey can you please come down here to take some pictures for me" ...lol...  I am glad I got to see it in person !  Congrats on your fish PC and clients !
Absolute beaut! I have an unhealthy infatuation with those fish.
nice fish
Awesome! Grew up in niagara and never took advantage of the upper river.

Fish was caught yesterday by a woman named Jan on the upper niagara river during a charter with Paul Castanelo, measured 24 plus inches and came in on the scales as 8 pounds even, huge smallie!    http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l1yU0WKkpEw&feature=player_embedded
Holy giant smallies!!  Nice looking fish too, beautiful markings.
That is amazing, what an absolute monster. Man do I ever need to get my butt in gear and get out there, I have a cousin who lives in Welland, and has recently gotten into fishing!
What a pig!!!
what a beauty! I've seen that guide's name (Paul Castanelo) before, maybe on bob Izumi or something. I guess it was definetly worth paying for a guide!
Awesome, and great shots!
I can,t take any credit as it was not caught by me but by the young lady in the pic!
WOWWY!  HOG!
INCREDIBLE!! Beauty fish.
WOW speechless
Awesome fish!!!!
A true trophy indeed!! Nice colors on her too!  JM
SWEET !!!
that sure thing is a BIG MAMA!... nice fish!...
Congratulations to Jan on hooking the bass of a lifetime!  And way to go gettin' 'er there, Paul!  A terrific day and some great photos to remember it.
Yes Paul Castellano has been on Bob's show as well as The Fishin' Canada show lately.  Cast Adventures   And yes that smallie is a giant!!!!
Holy crap that is a huge smallie for Erie let alone the river! Paul looks happier than the woman who caught it lol
Beautiful fish. Congrats to both the guide and the catcher.
Thats a monster looks like their strapping on the feed bag already
Care to share your technique (live bait, drop shot, tubes)???
That's a beauty fish!! Anywhere u go that's a trophy! Amazing river fish, beautiful colors. Congrats to the lady who landed it, can't even imagine the pull that thing had!!
Beautiful specimen! Hopefully they released that monster to allow it to get even larger!
Fish was released unharmed to be caught and grow bigger in the fall
